 A jet trainer crashed Sunday on the flight deck of the aircraft carrier Lexington in the Gulf of Mexico, killing five people, injuring at least two and damaging several aircraft, the Navy said.
 The crash of the two-seat T-2 Buckeye caused several fires on the World War II-era ship that sailors quickly brought under control, officials said.
 The crash also did major damage to two aircraft on the flight deck and minor damage to another, a Pentagon spokesman said.
 The Lexington, the Navy's oldest aircraft carrier, was 17 miles south of its home port of Pensacola when the accident occurred, Coast Guard Lt.
 The jet was assigned to Training Squadron 19, based at the Meridian, Miss., Naval Air Station, the Navy said.
